        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Mr. Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Albany</placeName>
                <add>?</add>
                <date>March 22 5610</date> A M<add>?</add></p>
            <p>Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am very sorry, that it was impossible<lb/> for me to go via
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> to <placeName>New York</placeName>, I<lb/>
                went by steamer from <placeName>Charleston</placeName> to <placeName>New
                    York</placeName>.<lb/> I am elected in <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, and I
                shall leave <placeName>Albany</placeName><lb/> the <date>15th of April</date>. I
                hope to do much good there,<lb/> for the people listened very attentively to my
                words.<lb/> I shall have now time enough to write, and I am<lb/> sure I will write
                now more for the Occident and<lb/> also for the Asmonean than the respective
                Editors<lb/> will feel inclined to publish. I had yet not<lb/> time to collect the
                money for the occident, but I shall<lb/> do it as soon as possible.</p>
            <p>I think, since I turned a <sic>portuguise</sic> jew, you are bound<lb/> to cheer me
                with two <add>תפילות</add> of this <add>מנהג</add> one for me,<lb/> and one for my
                wife.</p>
            <p>I found the occident in almost every house in <placeName>Charleston</placeName>,<lb/>
                and it was chiefly through its columns, that I was<lb/> recommended to the people,
                for which I am very<lb/> grateful to you.</p>
            <p><persName>Dr. Raphael</persName> is an orator, a poet, an original<lb/>
                <sic>geneius</sic>; but no scholar as I thought him to be.<lb/> There is much in his
                lectures that could be <sic>criticised</sic>, but I have no desire to do it, since I
                doubt, that<lb/> any good can result of it.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>I will write you more next, for now <sic>recieve</sic><lb/> the assurance of my best
                friendship</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Dr Wise</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
